text.tspan: "What am I but a lone fish
improvise, approximating density of vocal grains
One bug on a tree branch"
Yet I find peace in knowing
That I am not the only one looking"
3. Small diaphragm condenser microphone for flute.
4. A USB foot pedal set to output spaces.
5. The patch. Download from here: https://github.com/tellmewyatt/dizi.
3. Hit Ctrl/Cmd+A in the code view to select all the text.
4. Hit Ctrl/Cmd+Enter. A window should appear. Click on it.
5. Press your foot pedal to start the piece on the first patch.
You play the black parts, while the computer plays the red parts.
The score is played left to right, top to bottom.
The large numbers indicate cues (played with foot pedal).
The lines are not meant to indicate a specific melody or melodic shape,
just to indicate the general kind of material that can be played.
